Tracking Contact Reasons with Einstein Conversation Mining

Identify the top reasons your customers contact you with machine learning and conversation data. And boost your bot experience with automatic intents.

Einstein Conversation Mining works by reviewing conversation data, extracting the contact reason, and grouping it into categories. Reports show key characteristics for each contact reason: average conversation frequency and average number of conversation turns to completion. Contact reasons with high frequency and low turns are opportunities for automation.

Conversation turns refer to the back-and-forth between a customer and an agent. A report can filter conversations based on date or any field in the channel record. We recommend building multiple reports based on different parameters.

After creating a report, you can view it and act on the results. In Einstein Conversation Mining, you can send excerpts to a bot intent, then convert them into utterances tied to an intent. You can access Einstein Conversation Mining reports to build bots or add dialogs in Einstein Bot Builder.

Enable Einstein Conversation Mining
Build an Einstein Conversation Mining Report
Einstein Conversation Mining Report Results
Guidelines and Limits for Einstein Conversation Mining Data

Topics are groups of contact reasons that live in the same category. You can view details about topics, then view contact reasons inside each topic. Download data on topics to see all associated contact reasons or download excerpts related to each contact reason.

See also: Trailhead: Einstein Conversation Mining Report Creation
